The paper deals with the use of deep learning techniques for image classification and retrieval in the medical domain, specifically for dermatoscopic images. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. Additionally, the use of content-based image retrieval (CBIR) and the comparison with neural network-based classification methods suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories. The evaluation of diagnostic accuracy and the potential clinical applications of the proposed method suggest that the paper may also be relevant to the machine learning (cs.LG) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-categories.
